<subSubSection id="D7AB34F9FF9A48398BB461BAA294FB6B" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" type="description">
<paragraph id="9F0E6772FF9A48398BB461BAA549FBA2" blockId="3.[151,1059,926,1065]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">
C o m m e n t: In the original description, which is based on a unique female (erroneously sexed as a male) from &quot;Cauc. Min. Bor., Trialetskij Chreb, Bakuriani, 
<quantity id="5849CA97FF9A48398896619FA1E9FC65" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" unit="m" value="2000.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="1800.0">1800-2200 m</quantity>
&quot;, 
<bibRefCitation id="FB201A83FF9A48398BE461FDA00BFC64" author="PACE R" box="[199,332,985,1007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" pagination="7 - 43" refId="ref6818" refString="PACE R. (1996): Descrizione di nuove specie e sottospecie del genere Geostiba (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino dell'Associazione Romana di Entomologia 50 [1995]: 7 - 43." type="journal article" year="1996">PACE (1996)</bibRefCitation>
assigned the species to 
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A4839897B61FDA3B4FC65" box="[600,755,985,1006]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Lioglutosipalia</emphasis>
SCHEERPELTZ, 1951, now a synonym of 
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A48398A0161D2A0D8FB80" box="[290,415,1014,1035]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Sipalotricha</emphasis>
SCHEERPELTZ, 1931. Based on a revision of the 
<typeStatus id="400AD9D0FF9A483988E061D2A559FB87" box="[963,1054,1014,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FB201A83FF9A48398BB46637A060FBA2" author="ASSING V" box="[151,295,1043,1065]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" pagination="903 - 1006" refId="ref6482" refString="ASSING V. (2005): A revision of the species of Geostiba THOMSON and Tropimenelytron PACE of the Eastern Mediterranean, the Caucasus, and adjacent regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 37 (2): 903 - 1006." type="journal article" year="2005">Assing (2005)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="58B11CF1FF9A48398A5A6630A0A6FBA3" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1996" box="[377,481,1043,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zerchei">
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A48398A5A6630A0A6FBA3" box="[377,481,1043,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">G. zerchei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species of doubtful status and moved it to 
<taxonomicName id="58B11CF1FF9A483988E36637A54FFBA3" box="[960,1032,1043,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sibiota">
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A483988E36637A54FFBA3" box="[960,1032,1043,1064]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Sibiota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F0E6772FF9A48398BB4661DA294FB6B" blockId="3.[151,1058,1081,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">
During a field trip to Southwest 
<collectingCountry id="E7A627E2FF9A48398AC8661DA378FBC4" box="[491,575,1081,1103]" name="Georgia" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, Michael Schülke and the author succeeded in collecting a series of specimens including males in the environs of the 
<typeStatus id="400AD9D0FF9A4839884F6673A2DFFBE7" box="[876,920,1111,1132]" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">type</typeStatus>
locality, thus rendering a clarification of the identity of 
<taxonomicName id="58B11CF1FF9A4839896B6650A3F6FB03" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1996" box="[584,689,1139,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="720" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zerchei">
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A4839896B6650A3F6FB03" box="[584,689,1139,1161]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">G. zerchei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
finally possible. An examination of the males revealed that the species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="58B11CF1FF9A483989F066B5A25CFB2D" box="[723,795,1169,1190]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geostiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="717" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Sibiota">
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A483989F066B5A25CFB2D" box="[723,795,1169,1190]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Sibiota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but to 
<emphasis id="ADC5BB60FF9A4839884C66B5A2ABFB2D" box="[879,1004,1169,1190]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Sipalotricha</emphasis>
. The male is characterized by a pronounced sutural carina on the elytra (unique in the subgenus) (
<figureCitation id="078A7BF7FF9A48398A2F66EFA00DFB6A" box="[268,330,1227,1249]" captionStart="Figs 8-14" captionStartId="5.[151,191,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[162,1059,199,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1059,199,1483]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 8-14: Geostiba zerchei (8-12) and G. kakhetiana (13-14): (8, 13) male habitus; (9, 14) male forebody; (10-11) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (12) spermatheca. Scale bars: 8, 13: 1.0 mm; 9, 14: 0.5 mm; 10-12: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3738437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3738437/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). The external and sexual characters are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="078A7BF7FF9A4839884F66EFA288FB6B" box="[876,975,1227,1249]" captionStart="Figs 8-14" captionStartId="5.[151,191,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[162,1059,199,1479]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1059,199,1483]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 8-14: Geostiba zerchei (8-12) and G. kakhetiana (13-14): (8, 13) male habitus; (9, 14) male forebody; (10-11) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (12) spermatheca. Scale bars: 8, 13: 1.0 mm; 9, 14: 0.5 mm; 10-12: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3738437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3738437/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="720">Figs 8-12</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
